commit.message:
Add ability to hook into word completion to allow display customisation

This change improves flexibility for customising word completion.
Users can listen for word completion events and specify how to
display completion suggestions for the currently edited word. For
example, to display completion suggestions as a list before the
edited line or as a menu below the word being completed.
Add support for cancelling word completion
Add ability to cycle through word completions in reverse order
Add support for adding a custom suffix to suggested word completion

Add ability to complete words

Continued pressing of the tab key inserts the next completion suggestion
into a line. When all completion suggestions are exhausted, the original
word is restored back.
Add Completions for storing and navigating completion suggestions
Add to Line the ability to find a word to complete before the cursor
Change Line to calculate prompt size once to improve performance
Change Reader to stop listening to key events and improve performance
Add the ability to specify keys to exit input without using the enter key
Add test to ensure history duplicates configuration affects line editing
Add support for preserving edits to lines stored in history
Fix navigation to the previous history line to display the latest line
Add the ability to replace the current line in the history buffer
Change to extract key name lookup to improve readability and performance
Add performance tests for line reading to check speed and objects allocation
Add rspec-benchmark to development dependencies
Add rake task for running performance tests
Add new issue templates workflow to replace the old version
Change CI workflow to allow bundler version configuration
Change pull request template to improve requirements list formatting
Add release notes
Change coveralls dependency to allow sending coverage data
Add configuration option to set the maximum history size
Change to finish input with a newline when enter is pressed inside the line
Add to line the ability to find a chars range and a word under the cursor
Change gemspec to relax rspec version upper boundary
Add website link to the license
Change release date
Change rubocop to ignore linting debuggers
